    "en": {
      "title": "Sapugaskand refinery to continue operations",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st); The Ministry of Power and Energy says that it will take steps to continue operating the Sapugaskanda Oil Refinery.",
        "A senior official of the Ministry said that another crude oil ship will arrive in the country today (26) or tomorrow (27).",
        "When inquired considering whether there is a shortage of fuel in the country, a senior official in the Ministry emphasized that sufficient stocks of fuel are available to meet the local demand.",
        "The shortage of fuel reported in the Puttalam and Kurunegala Districts has been addressed to a greater extent.",
        "Military should be ready for technological knowledge for cyber warfare \u2013 President",
        "Is Sri Lanka\u2019s economic crisis spiraling into a humanitarian one?"
      ],
